5:
All right, who's hungry? For dinner,
we've got chicken marinated
in tomato sauce.
8:
Ooh! Another mouth-watering meal—
and fancier than our usual fare.
11:
Having access to Palpebra now makes
it easy to buy all sorts of ingredients.
It's nice having so many options!
15: Wait... Where is the tiger man—Nimbus?
18: Oh... He said he wasn't hungry.
22:
A lot happened. He has plenty of food
for thought; give him time to stomach
that first.
28:
Hmm... I saw him eating some fruit
earlier. You know, the really sour ones
that grow around town?
34:
To think that whole damn desert is just
a puny little dot in the sky now...
36:
And I'm... from one of those dots?
Hmph, what's it even matter though?
Not like I can call it "home."
45:
Oh, uh... Stella, was it? What do you
want?
52:
What? Oh, food?
I already SAID I'm not—
54: Sigh. All right. Guess I could eat it...
67: Didn't taste test it, did you? Try it.
78:
I read that cooking fruit makes it
sweeter. I wonder why it didn't work?
82:
...Fruit? Wait, that—that black lump
of charcoal was FRUIT?
You've gotta be kidding...
86:
Yes. Please disregard it. Alk made
dinner, so please eat that instead.
92:
Alk is a phenomenal cook. Please be
assured, he doesn't make mistakes
like this.
99:
Alk is a PHENOMENAL cook.
You should try his food!
104:
...Tch. I'm not REALLY doin' this, am I?
Here goes nothing...
117:
What are you doing? Skulking around
in the dark like that...
119:
If you were hungry, you could have
eaten supper with everyone else.
123:
I-It's not like I'm eatin' it cause I want to.
That girl—Stella—she made me do it!
126:
Oh? My mistake, then. From the way you
were gobbling everything down,
it looked like you were enjoying yourself.
130:
...All right, you got me.
Food like this was hard to come by
in the desert.
132:
It's just... I don't know. Home-made
meals and a warm bed? That's not the
kinda life I'm used to livin'.
135:
I heard you used to be a hell of a
warrior yourself... Don't you ever get
restless playin' house with those two?
137:
Are you really going off on their little
adventure? Who knows what could
happen to you—to them.
140:
...Well, I have you to watch my back,
do I not?
143:
Hah, you're joking, right? I've got no
reason to stick my neck out for you. If
the goin gets tough, you're on your own.
149:
Would your pride allow you to abandon
an ally in need? No, I think not.
151: I'm trusting you with those two, Nimbus.
